Imagine the mouse is on a flat surface and you are looking down from the top,
with the 3dconnexion logo at the bottom of the mouse, closest to you. 

Axis 0: x axis  + <-left---right-> - 
Axis 1: y axis  + <-backwards---forwards-> - (where backwards is towards the logo)
Axis 2: z axis  + <-down---up-> - (where down is vertically towards the surface)
Axis 3: x rot   + <-pitch forward---pitch backwards-> -
Axis 4: y rot   + <-pitch left---pitch right-> -
Axis 5: z rot   - <-counterclockwise---clockwise-> +

Button 1: left side
Button 2: right side
